data.description: Role of administration in American government; problems of organization, bureaucracy and control; public policy as the output of the administrative process.
data.title: PUBLIC MANAGEMENT

data.description: Examines how managers in public and not-for-profit agencies can secure and utilize legal authority, human resources, and funds to accomplish organizational goals. Includes strategies for establishing and maintaining effective external relations and for working through other organizations to accomplish objectives.
data.title: ADVANCED PUBLIC MANAGEMENT: CRAFT, CONSTRAINTS AND ACCOUNTABILITY
